</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CC64452C4E7AF7EDD28CC74AEA64C529" pageId="276" pageNumber="277" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="6A4A66EC4C23F8FAA6D0ECF95DB5EED9" pageId="276" pageNumber="277">
<taxonomicName id="C9B7F9EF37A0CBE0065FDE87046914D6" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Scarites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="276" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subterraneus">Scarites subterraneus</taxonomicName>
Fabricius, 1775: 249. Type locality: &quot;P[oin]t Pelee, Ont[ario]&quot; (neotype label). Neotype (♂), designated by Nichols (1985a: 1214), in CNC [# 20654]. Note. 
<normalizedToken id="17051B5A236B6DD6DC3648EA4DD9CBA4" originalValue="“America”">&quot;America&quot;</normalizedToken>
was the area originally listed by Fabricius (1775: 249).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6A350EE0DAFF81B49B145B5F3F355651" pageId="276" pageNumber="277">
<taxonomicName id="59C44C952EE7FBF26E27F3C241D5BAA7" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="276" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="interruptus">Carabus interruptus</taxonomicName>
Herbst, 1784: 133. Type locality: 
<normalizedToken id="F9E51411FCD626C5940F56BDF016F8D5" originalValue="«Ostindien»">&quot;Ostindien&quot;</normalizedToken>
(original citation), which is incorrect. Syntype(s) location unknown (possibly in ZMHB). Synonymy established by Fabricius (1801: 124).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="78C9A746484265A2C2C09CD782F6871B" pageId="276" pageNumber="277">
<taxonomicName id="754B39926CA8218316998DDEA382D0BC" authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1813" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Scarites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="276" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subterreus">Scarites subterreus</taxonomicName>
Bonelli, 1813: 466. Type locality: 
<normalizedToken id="D944421948FACB71D65089529C2CA802" originalValue="«Amérique">&quot;Amerique</normalizedToken>
septentrionale&quot; (original citation). Syntype(s) location unknown. Synonymy established by Chaudoir (1881: 94).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F4ED86C8BF67E8DC851C5CAA593DE5B3" pageId="276" pageNumber="277">
<taxonomicName id="2158154AAF1EEFC109F52ACEC2D29670" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1827" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Scarites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="276" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beckwithii">Scarites beckwithii</taxonomicName>
Stephens, 1827: 37. Type locality: &quot;near Dover [and] Yorkshire coast [United Kingdom]&quot; (original citation). Syntype(s) [3 originally cited] in BMNH. Synonymy established with doubt by Chaudoir (1855: 104), confirmed by Nichols (1988a: 48).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF059F158A35E4F2280AB82D6DB13C6B" pageId="276" pageNumber="277">
<taxonomicName id="C2A40DAB66AA8CAE4A3A5AC940629988" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1843" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Scarites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="276" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="denticollis">Scarites denticollis</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir, 1843b: 729. Type locality: &quot;Nouvelle 
<normalizedToken id="40297659E1A0DAA811BBC7DE9A2CE6DA" originalValue="Orléans">Orleans</normalizedToken>
[Orleans Parish, Louisiana]&quot; (original citation). Syntype(s) in MHNP. Synonymy established by Chaudoir (1881: 94), confirmed by Nichols (1988a: 48).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D7915FCD7FF8703CB7A2F0D6E2A5038" pageId="276" pageNumber="277">
<taxonomicName id="55839004C4448B8DF4124EEC932AC1F0" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1845" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Scarites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="276" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patruelis">Scarites patruelis</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1845a: 201. Type locality: 
<normalizedToken id="E3443C02E365986901EC78A229ECCA91" originalValue="«Georgia»">&quot;Georgia&quot;</normalizedToken>
(original citation). Syntype(s) in MCZ [# 673]. Synonymy established with doubt, under the name 
<taxonomicName id="B350080A7B038592438DA05D18FF0D12" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1843" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Scarites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="276" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="denticollis">
<emphasis id="8240953A077F05AC621D818E1A5C969D" italics="true" pageId="276" pageNumber="277">Scarites denticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir, by Chaudoir (1855: 104).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5A6F65F56457EBC7805CE1C3DD6F79AE" pageId="276" pageNumber="277">
<taxonomicName id="4E5DAD0F45D98DF0739B54D5897305B8" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Scarites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="276" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="californicus">Scarites californicus</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1852a: 198. Type locality: &quot;ad San Diego [San Diego County, California]&quot; (original citation). Syntype(s) [2 originally cited] in MCZ [# 672]. Synonymy established by Bousquet and Larochelle (1993: 97) based on Nichols (1988a: 49) unpublished thesis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="70CEACF5893AD5021A971CB93272D71B" pageId="276" pageNumber="277">
<taxonomicName id="0D6A52768269FE35B14765A32C26458F" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1881" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Scarites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="276" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="texanus">Scarites texanus</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir, 1881: 94. Type locality: &quot;Texas et dans le Yucatan (?)&quot; (original citation). Syntype(s) in MHNP (Nichols 1988a: 51). Synonymy established by Nichols (in Bousquet and Skelley 2010: 47).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC715C8BD7B3B9478BA5A08E54B9A75B" pageId="276" pageNumber="277">
<taxonomicName id="2F9F7052720058009BBF4E27736B8D32" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1891" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Scarites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="276" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="durangoensis">Scarites durangoensis</taxonomicName>
Bates, 1891a: 232. Type locality: &quot;Villa Lerdo in Durango [Mexico]&quot; (original citation). Syntype(s) probably in BMNH. Synonymy established, under the name 
<taxonomicName id="6207D93AF1B739060A1766BCDC603FD0" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Scarites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="276" pageNumber="277" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="californicus">
<emphasis id="F44FB12CB69523F77C97848AFD1BF9E3" italics="true" pageId="276" pageNumber="277">Scarites californicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
LeConte, by 
<normalizedToken id="E69262735C4F7642F13EC63903051C18" originalValue="Bänninger">Baenninger</normalizedToken>
(1933: 119).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="80E44DC3880FF3FC86C2F81D2D12B374" lastPageId="277" lastPageNumber="278" pageId="276" pageNumber="277" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6F96D259BAB99E6D0FD51116355D4F62" pageId="276" pageNumber="277">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="94D84CB5885B81B1A90CBDDE48C8BB7F" lastPageId="277" lastPageNumber="278" pageId="276" pageNumber="277">
This species is found from southeastern New Hampshire (Rockingham and Strafford Counties, Donald S. Chandler pers. comm. 2008) to eastern North Dakota (Cass County, Donald P. Schwert pers. comm. 1989), including southern Ontario (Lindroth 1961a: 129), south to the 
<normalizedToken id="DEC95E251F7C450081403EFBF069502B" originalValue="Yucatán">Yucatan</normalizedToken>
Peninsula (Nichols 1988a: 52), the 
<pageBreakToken id="34AA82A87BA7F47C793EFB14ABD1E677" pageId="277" pageNumber="278" start="start">Florida</pageBreakToken>
Keys (Peck and Thomas 1998: 17), and Cuba (Darlington 1934: 67; Nichols 1988b: Fig. 5-8), west along the southwest to southwestern California (LeConte, 1852a: 198, as 
<taxonomicName id="BF18EE625C29AF9B386BFD0D427E5C98" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Scarites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="277" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="californicus">
<emphasis id="05A1DA9806224795E97B977600FD8598" italics="true" pageId="277" pageNumber="278">Scarites californicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and Baja California (Horn 1894: 307).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
